'''Molecular shielding''', also known as a '''molecular shield''', was a special type of [[Deflector shield/Legends|deflector shield]]. It was an experimental technology that was capable of absorbing the energy of an incoming [[Laser/Legends|laser]] blast and then funnelling it into [[Power cell/Legends|power cells]].<ref name="EGTD">''[[The Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref>

The ''[[Star Home]]'', the transport of the [[Hapan]] [[Queen Mother]] utilized a unique molecular shielding system to reinforce its hollowed out [[Basalt/Legends|basalt]] base.<ref name="EGVV">''[[The Essential Guide to Vehicles and Vessels]]''</ref>

This advanced technology was developed in [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]], and was heavily used by [[X-1 Viper]] [[Droid/Legends|droids]] as a full coverage energy shell. The energy that was absorbed by the shield was used to power the [[Droid/Legends|droid's]] multiple weapon systems.<ref name="EGTD" />

As a result the molecular shielding installed on these droids made them extremely durable, and the X-1 Viper was considered essentially invulnerable to all short-range energy weapons and [[Artillery/Legends|artillery]] pieces. While able to absorb and convert high grade weapons fire - such as [[Ion cannon/Legends|ion cannons]], turbolasers, and energy torpedoes - the molecular shielding could be overwhelmed by such fire, though it still required an inordinate amount of firepower to do so.

Despite the extreme durability of molecular shielding, the shields only absorbed energy based attacks, and were worthless against a physical attack; X-1's were thus helpless when the reborn [[Palpatine/Legends|Emperor's]] [[Chrysalide]] beasts tore into them, completely bypassing their shields.

